result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy E. Kleinschmidt was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver THC (>10,000g) [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit, Second and Subsequent Offense], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(h)5.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

PLEA: Ct. 1 (Deliver THC (>10,000g)/Conspiracy to Commit/2nd and subsequent)>>NO CONTEST. 

COURT advises def of rights (including constitutional rights) & penalties & ques def to understanding.  
COURT finds plea & waiver of rights freely & vol made, a factual basis, & def guilty. 
Def makes statement. 

COURT ORDERS: 4 years prison - 2 years IC and 2 years ES - CONDITIONS of ES: assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the dept; maintain absolute sobriety; maintain fulltime employment/schooling/combination of the 2 or if not, make good faith effort to obtain fulltime status; DNA sample and surcharge; CC. 
COURT finds the def entitled to 754 days sentence credit for time already served. 
COURT finds the def eligible for SAP and NOT eligible for CIP. 
COURT remands def to sheriff's dept so sentence handed down by the Court may proceed.

(bond modification)

AMENDED:  $250,000.00 signature bond the first $25,000.00 component of which shall be cash.  Defendant is to be deemed eligible for the Electronic Monitoring Program condition while on pretrial bond and without need to post the cash component through the Marathon County Jail if he satisfactorily meets the jail criteria for that program.  It is also anticipated that while on the Electronic Monitoring Program, the defendant will be able to continue his emplyment, and that he be allowed to continue his treatment schedule.  While the Defendant will not be required to post the cash component, it is expected that he will sign the signature bond component before being released on the Electronic Monitoring Program.  All other conditions of the defendant's bond are to remain the same - Defendant and defendant's ID card be released out on bond to Rick T. Cveykus of Cveykus Law Office to attend Koinonia Residential Treatment Facility.  If defendant vacates/leaves Koinonia Residential Treatment Facility at any time, without authorization from the Court and/or Koinonia Residential Treatment Facility, he can be charged criminally and is to report to Marathon County Jail immediately.  No contact with victim(s): S.K. Contact includes direct personal or physical and indirect contact by phone, in writing of any kind, entry to the person's residence or place of employment together with contacts through other persons.  Contact, however, may be made through the defendant's attorney.  No prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
